  "prompt": "What is the best site to download songs?",
  "response": "There are a variety of platforms where you can download music legally, depending on what you're looking for. Here are a few of the best options:\n\n1. **Amazon Music**: Offers a wide selection of songs and albums available for purchase and download.\n\n2. **iTunes Store**: Provides a vast library of music you can buy and download to your devices.\n\n3. **Bandcamp**: Great for independent artists; allows you to purchase music directly from the artist, often in various file formats.\n\n4. **Beatport**: Ideal for electronic music fans, offering high-quality tracks for purchase and download.\n\n5. **7digital**: Offers a large catalog of music across various genres, available for purchase and download in high-quality formats.\n\n6. **Google Play Music** (Note: This has been largely replaced by YouTube Music, but previously purchased music is often still accessible.)\n\n7. **Jamendo**: Provides free music downloads from independent artists, mostly under Creative Commons licenses.\n\n8. **SoundCloud**: Some artists provide their tracks for free download, although many require payment or a subscription.\n\nRemember always to use legal channels for downloading music to support the artists and ensure you're complying with copyright laws.",
